    "causal_summary": "The `create:changelog` command generates changelog markdown files but stops there. Publishing a GitHub release requires separate manual steps: create a git tag, push it, then run `gh release create` with properly formatted release notes. Users must do this every time after running the changelog command, which is error-prone and creates a gap where a changelog exists locally but no GitHub release has been published.",
